<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Aged" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Aged,</orth> old, of things as well as persons: <bibl n="shak. luc 855" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 855</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.3.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 3, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.72" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.74" default="NO" valid="yes">2, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 6</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.5.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 5, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.178" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 178</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 23</bibl>. 59 (Q<hi rend="sub">2</hi> Ff <emph>noble</emph>). <bibl n="shak. tit 4.4.96" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 96</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.130" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.175" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 175</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 2, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.4.28" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.1.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 1, 157</bibl>. <emph>our a.</emph> == our old men, <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.179" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 179</bibl>. <cit><quote>a. things,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 941" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 941</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a. ears,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 2.74" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 74</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a. custom,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.176" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 176</bibl></cit>. <emph>to be a. in any kind of course</emph> == to adhere to old customs, <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.238" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 238</bibl>, cf. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 3, 8</bibl>.<lb /><emph>A. cramps</emph> == cramps such as old people are wont to suffer, <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.261" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 261</bibl> (cf. <bibl n="shak. luc 855" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 855</bibl>, and <emph>Old</emph>). <emph>my a. eloquence</emph> == the eloquence of my age, <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.83" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. III, 1, 83</bibl>. <emph>a. honour</emph> == honour in age, <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.216" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 3, 216</bibl>. <cit><quote>a. contusions,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.3.3" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 3, 3</bibl></cit>. <emph>a. night</emph> == night of old age, <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.16" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 16</bibl>.* <cit><quote>a. wrinkles,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 7</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a. tyranny,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 52</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a. patience,</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 2.4.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 4, 48</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>